@*
    HOME PAGE — Blazor Concept: NavigationManager + OnInitializedAsync Lifecycle

    React equivalent: Navigate component — <Navigate to="/basic-queries" replace />
    Angular equivalent: Router redirect — { path: '', redirectTo: '/basic-queries' }

    Key Blazor concepts:
    1. @page "/" — Route directive, registers this component for the root URL
       React:  <Route path="/" element={<Navigate to="/basic-queries" />} />
       Angular: { path: '', redirectTo: '/basic-queries', pathMatch: 'full' }

    2. @inject NavigationManager Nav — DI for navigation service
       React:  const navigate = useNavigate()
       Angular: private router = inject(Router)

    3. OnInitializedAsync() — Lifecycle method, runs when component initializes
       React:  useEffect(() => { navigate('/basic-queries') }, [])
       Angular: ngOnInit() { this.router.navigate(['/basic-queries']) }

       Blazor lifecycle methods:
       - OnInitialized() / OnInitializedAsync() — runs once on first render
       - OnParametersSet() / OnParametersSetAsync() — runs when params change
       - OnAfterRender() / OnAfterRenderAsync() — runs after DOM update

    4. Nav.NavigateTo() — Programmatic navigation
       Blazor:  Nav.NavigateTo("/basic-queries")
       React:   navigate('/basic-queries')
       Angular: this.router.navigate(['/basic-queries'])
*@
@page "/"
@inject NavigationManager Nav

@code {
    // OnInitializedAsync — lifecycle hook that runs when the component first loads
    // This is the most common lifecycle method (like React's useEffect with empty deps)
    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        // Redirect to the first demo page
        Nav.NavigateTo("/basic-queries");
    }
}
